# USER.md

Personal preferences, style choices, and stable facts about the user.
Unlike `MEMORY.md` (project facts) and `LESSONS.md` (action-triggered advice),
this file holds durable first-person preferences that apply across projects
and sessions — "user prefers X", "user's style is Y", "user dislikes Z".

Entries use the same `### heading` + blank line + body + `tags:` format as
`MEMORY.md`. Kept small on purpose (default cap: 1536 bytes) so it loads
cheaply into every session.

